<Author>purebob
<Content>From old Hanoi to East Berlin - Purebob involved again ! Stayed at the Mueggelsee hotel for a conference.Firstly - know that this hotel is in East Berlin as was - and it is an hour's schlep in a taxi from the airport to get here. It is no mean feat to go to the town centre to dine, for example, so you are pretty much stranded here.Hotel is set in lush forest at the edge of Lake Mueggel. Almost all rooms seemed to have great views.Check in and pubic areas all very impressive in this hotel - spacious, interesting and well kept. Bar quite intimate a fun, although the service from very young and indolent waitresses bordered on unacceptable. My room was very spacious and comfortable with a patio area overlooking the forest. Very nice indeed.Bed a bit soft and pillows VERY soft, but perhaps that is the personal preference of other folks.The conference food was quite decent.Best of all was the bowling alley in the basement ! Much fun was had here during the conference evenings ! I did not try the swimming pool or gym.It was a fine conference hotel, and I can imagine it is a peaceful retreat for folks wanting a quit civilised break by the lake too.Just don't expect to be close enough to Berlin to spend much time there from thid hotel. 
